title: SpaceX to break pad turnaround record in support of Starlink
summary: To launch another pair of Starlink stacks to orbit this week, SpaceX will break its all-time launch pad turnaround record. The first launch, Starlink Group 5-4, is currently scheduled to lift off at 12:10 AM EST (05:10 UTC) on Sunday, Feb. 12, pending a forecasted 20% chance of acceptable weather.

title: Russian cargo ship docks as second Progress suffers sudden loss of coolant
summary: A Russian Progress supply ship successfully docked with the International Space Station early Saturday but in an unlikely, presumed coincidence, another Progress, docked at a different port, suffered a sudden loss of coolant similar to an incident that disabled a Soyuz crew ship in December.

title: Another Russian spacecraft docked to the space station is leaking
summary: None of this will comfort NASA as it partners with Russia on the space station.

title: Progress MS-22 arrives at ISS, MS-21 develops coolant loop leak
summary: Roscosmos’ latest Progress resupply craft has docked at the International Space Station (ISS). Liftoff of the Progress MS-22 mission occurred at 06:15 UTC on Feb. 9 from Site 31/6 at the Baikonur Cosmodrome in Kazakhstan aboard a Soyuz-2.1a rocket, docking two days later on Feb. 11 at 08:45 UTC.

title: Astronaut Sen. Kelly touts ‘stunning’ space business growth, calls for more rocket competition
summary: Arizona Senator Mark Kelly, who flew to space four times over a 15-year career as an astronaut, praised the growth of the industry and gave a rallying cry for intensified competition.
